                        <interp inst="t18760808-name-290" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BUTCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grainer, of 2, Park Terrace, Rotherhithe—I was a witness in the case of Jones <hi rend="italic">v.</hi> Coombe—I received 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. with the subpoena that was left at my house, about 11 o'clock one evening—I did not receive the other part of the five guineas until yesterday.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> I know the defendant perfectly well—I would have trusted him—I never knew anything bad of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">By</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">THE COURT</hi>, He never said anything to me about it—I had not made any claim for my expenses; it was brought to me yesterday—I had applied to Mr. Preston for it, and he treated me more like a dog than a human being. '</p>
